The paper discusses issues and solutions related to wireless ad hoc networks, which primarily fall under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses various models of ad hoc networks, such as ad hoc grids, ad hoc clouds, wireless mesh networks, and cognitive radio ad hoc networks, which involve aspects of information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these sub-categories are likely to be relevant to the paper.
